                <h1>Unlocking Mental Health: Characterization in "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>In "The Yellow Wallpaper," characterization is pivotal, illustrating the protagonist's descent into madness. The narrator, confined to a room, struggles against societal repression and her deteriorating mental state. Her obsession with the wallpaper symbolizes her quest for identity and freedom, reflecting broader themes of women's oppression in the 19th century.</p>
